<div id="country3" class="tabcontent">
<div style="width: 740px; border: 1px dashed gray; padding: 10px;  margin:0px auto;">

<h2>Books/Journal Issue Entry</h2>
<hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
This screen captures the Library modify Books/Journal Issue Entry details.

<br />
<hr /><br />
<img src="images/Lib_IssueBookSearch.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr /><br />
<img src="images/Lib_IssueBookDetails.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />
<p>
<span class="title">Search (Button): </span><br />
    User can search the records based on issue no., service no., issue date.Select the particuler search criteria from the option button.
<br />
<span class="title">GRID (Display): </span> <br />
   Based on search criteria data will display in the form of table. At a time only five (5) records will be displayed. To navigate or look for the next record pagination (the system of numbering pages) will be there. 
<br />
    <span class="title">OK Button and: </span> 
    <br />If user wants to switch directly to any particular page no, then he can simply enter the page no. in the given and click on Ok Button.
<br />
<span class="title">Issue No.: </span><br />
This Field is autogenerated.
<br />
<span class="title">Issue Date: </span> <br />
   User can update Issue Date in this by clicking on the calender given on the side of the box, it can't remain blank.
<br />
    <span class="title"> Service Number: </span> 
    <br />User can update Service Number from the given list, it can't remain blank.
<br />
     <span class="title"> Name: </span> 
    <br />User can update Name details.
<br />
    <span class="title">Rank:</span> 
    <br />User can update Rank details.
<br />
    <span class="title">Issued By:</span> 
    <br />User can select Issued By from the given list, it can't remain blank.
<br />

    <span class="title">Add (Button): </span> 
    <br />User can Add a new row by clicking on this button to add the Books detail.
<br />
    <span class="title">Delete(Button): </span> 
    <br />User can Delete the row by clicking on this button.
<br />
   <span class="title">Account No.: </span> 
    <br />User can update Account Nubmer details.
<br />
     <span class="title">Name of Book: </span> 
    <br />User can update Name of Book details.
<br />
    <span class="title">Quantity: </span> 
    <br />User can update Quantity details.
<br />
    <span class="title">Update (Button): </span> 
    <br />By clicking on Update button user can update the data.
<br />
    <span class="title">Reset (Button): </span> 
    <br />Clicking on reset button, will clear the current or existing data.
<br />
  </p>
</div>
